sentences: The K-Otics were a college band formed at Troy University in Troy, Alabama circa 1962.
The K-Otics disbanded in 1967 with Tommy Mann entering the business world while Ray Goss became a barber and continued to play music locally in Montgomery.
Ken Murphy - Lead guitar, Backing vocals                            1962-64
Kim Venable - Drums (later with Classics IV)                    1964-67
Ed Sanford - Keyboards (later with Sanford-Townsend Band)       1964
Lawrence Shaul - Keyboards (later with Classics IV)             1966-67
